Currently I am using

    vscode.commands.executeCommand('vscode.executeDefinitionProvider', uri, pos).then(refs => {

    });

on my [extension](https://github.com/anacierdem/vscode-requirejs) to re-invoke the provider recursively.

During this process I like to pass around a state object to keep track of the initiating point. Currently using a static value (`ReferenceProvider.childWord`) for this, which is not appropriate as it is possible to enqueue other providers during any asynchronous operation that will overwrite this value.

I suggest;

    vscode.languages.registerDefinitionProvider(
                { scheme: 'file' }, 
                new ReferenceProvider(),
                "providerIdentifier"
            )

    vscode.commands.executeCommand('vscode.executeDefinitionProvider', uri, pos, extraParams).then(refs => {

    });

Where;

    extraParams = {
        "id": "providerIdentifier",
        "customParam1": "value",
        ...
    }

vscode API then should check if providerIdentifier is registered and pass custom params when it is being invoked. This will make it possible to use persistent states with this recursive strategy.
